Problem 2 
Question:

When you run:

kubectl apply -f pod.yaml

Explain the full flow inside Kubernetes.

Which components are involved?

Solution:-
When you run:

kubectl apply -f pod.yaml
Step-by-step flow:

1️⃣ kubectl
→ Sends request to API Server

2️⃣ API Server
→ Validates YAML
→ Stores desired state in etcd

3️⃣ Controller Manager
→ Notices new Pod is needed
→ Ensures desired state is met

4️⃣ Scheduler
→ Chooses best node for the Pod

5️⃣ kubelet (on selected node)
→ Receives instruction
→ Talks to container runtime

6️⃣ Container Runtime (Docker/containerd)
→ Pulls image
→ Starts container

7️⃣ kube-proxy
→ Handles networking

💡 Golden Rule:
👉 Kubernetes is declarative
You say: “I want a pod”
Kubernetes figures out: “HOW to make it happen”
